column5: well i figure its time to breakout my 2006 great salmon derby prize bag.  ...and there sure is alot of good ones....my partner and myself won $1,000 bucks and prize bag full of salmon lures,and a tackle box,as well as some walleye spoons and some small spoons for brookies and rainbows..and a nice big lucky strike wide salmon net .this was for our week #2 3rd place finish for a 33.58lb chinook salmon,  so i thought i would take a few pics before i put them all in my salmon box,and i will be trying a few tommorow as i am going out on lake ontario in my buddys 32ft thompson out of port darlington....so i hope to have some real nice pics to share tommorow night....till then so here is a few pics   cheers
wow congrats on all of that, good luck tomorow
Wow, that's great!  Very nice looking stuff there.  Looking forward to seeing the ppics of the beauties some of those catch ya.  Maureen
FD the Silverstreaks are killlers for Kings...nice Win
Nice haul there Shawn!  I'm sure we'll be seeing a new PB fish caught with one of those beauties!! Good luck!
That is one great pack of prizes ... hope you got room for it all.   Congrats
Nice haul dude.  I'll be out with my two oldest Sunday morning, looking for salmon and trout.
there not gonna help you saturday evening, i am catching all the fish tonight
Wow your sure all set with that pack. Everything you'd ever need to get fishing. Congrats.
